						<p class="legal-footer--full-view-balance-footnote" style="display: none;" />
						<p>IMPORTANT: Disclosures are obtained from Fidelity.com and NetBenefits.com and may relate to accounts and features not available in this beta experience. You may review all disclosures relating to your accounts by returning to the Fidelity.com classic experience or logging on to NetBenefits.com.</p>
						<p>"<b>All Accounts</b>" equals the sum of the balances of the selected accounts identified in the account selector. These accounts may include your Fidelity personal and workplace accounts (excluding pension benefits), accounts managed by a third party adviser but held at Fidelity, and accounts accessible via the Full View service (identified as non-Fidelity accounts, if you have signed up for this service). Pension benefits are not included. Workplace account balances may include unvested amounts. Information regarding non-Fidelity accounts that are denominated in foreign currency or that hold positions in foreign currency may be  displayed on this page in USD.  You may view information for non-Fidelity accounts in its original foreign denomination using the FullView service.  Fidelity is not able to verify the accuracy, timeliness or completeness of information regarding accounts accessible via the Full View service.</p>
						<p>This information is provided as a convenience and is not a substitute for your Fidelity account statement, nor is it intended for trading purposes. Please consult your account statement, and any statements from the respective financial institution for the accounts provided for information regarding your account balance, positions, and transactions. This information may include assets that Fidelity does not hold on your behalf and which are obtained through the Full View service.</p>
						<p>Securities are priced real-time for customers that have agreed to the Real-Time Quotes Subscriber Agreements; otherwise, quotes are delayed at least 15 minutes. If the current market price is unavailable or the market is closed, Fidelity will factor in the most recent closing market price to determine the closing market value.</p>
						<p>Account balances containing only mutual fund positions or portfolios that are included in College Savings accounts are updated less frequently as they rely on transaction settlement periods for when money or shares are bought, sold, or transferred. Mutual fund distributions and capital gains can affect your account value and typically have a 1-3 business day settlement period before your account is updated.</p>
						<p>College Savings Portfolios are calculated using the prior business day's closing price.</p>
						<p>Annuities are priced as of the market close date on which the value per unit, income value, or withdrawal value for an annuity was last calculated.</p>
						<p># Annuity values do not reflect pending transactions. Final values will be posted later.</p>
						<p>++ Income and Payout Annuity contracts are not included in your total account value.</p>
						<p class="legal-footer--full-view-footnote" style="display: none;">Balances and holdings displayed for non-Fidelity accounts reflect information available on your account sites when last refreshed (including information from accounts that are denominated in foreign currency or that hold positions in foreign currency from your non-Fidelity accounts, if available). You may view information for non-Fidelity accounts in its original foreign denomination using the Full View service. Non-Fidelity account aggregation services provided by Yodlee, Inc., an independent company not affiliated with Fidelity Investments.</p>
						<p>Balances displayed for your accounts and positions reflect information available when your selected accounts were last refreshed. If you manually refresh only some of your accounts, the values shown for the positions in those accounts and the balances shown in the Account Selector for those accounts may be more up to date than accounts/positions that were not manually refreshed.</p>
						<p class="legal-footer--cash-available-to-withdraw" style="display: none;"><sup>†††</sup>Amount collected and available for immediate withdrawal. This balance includes both Core and other Fidelity Money Market funds held in each account listed within Manage Money & Payments. This balance does not include deposits that have not cleared. Sell orders are reflected in this balance on settlement date and Buy orders are reflected on trade date. Note: Within Manage Money & Payments charts, Health Savings Accounts (HSAs) are included in the non-IRA categories for Core and Non-Core Money Market Funds.</p>
						<p>The Stock Plans values displayed are arrived at using the prior business day closing price, or the cash value for cash based plans. Select the plan name for a complete description of the values shown. Values may be unvested, and may not reflect withdrawn assets. Please refer to the provisions in your individual Award Agreement and the official stock plan document which govern the terms of your award. The provisions in the Award Agreement and stock plan document supercede any information, including conflicting information, reflected on the website.</p>

						<p>Personal Rate of Return information for authorized Fidelity accounts will become available the monthly cycle following authorization. For periods less than one year, performance returns are presented on a cumulative basis.</p>
						<p>If your return information contains dashes '--', we either don't have a return for that time period, or your account is being validated. Accounts opened after the beginning of the year are excluded from the calculation.</p>
						<p>Your Personal Rate of Return is calculated using a money-weighted formula. It reflects the performance of the underlying investments in your eligible Fidelity accounts including dividends, interest, and fees; as well as the size and timing of your individual trades. If you use an account with cash management features, the Personal Rate of Return calculation may be affected by deposits, withdrawals, bill payment and other money movement transactions. Non-Fidelity accounts are excluded from the calculation. The Personal Rate of Return is an estimate only and should not be used solely in making investment decisions. It is calculated using Fidelity-provided information and information from third-party data sources and providers and therefore Fidelity cannot make any representations or guarantees as to its timeliness and accuracy. Fidelity will not provide notification that past data may have been inaccurate, or that it has been corrected.</p>
						<p>Personal Rate of Return (money-weighted) information may not be available for the following account types: Employer-Sponsored Retirement Plans (e.g., 401(k) plans), Brokerage Link accounts, Brokerage Flex accounts, certain insurance/annuity holdings, and stock plans. These accounts are also not included in the Rate of Return calculation for your entire portfolio appearing at the top of the Portfolio Summary page. Time-weighted returns are available for Employer-Sponsored Retirement Plans as of the end of the previous business day and can be accessed by See YTD Change link.</p>

						<p />Your Allocation Style is determined based on the rounded percentage of <b>equity holdings</b> in your selected accounts as follows:

						<p>Price improvement details provided for domestic stock and single leg option orders entered during market hours after the primary opening, provided there is a National Best Bid and Offer (NBBO) at the time the order is placed. Price improvement details are provided for informational purposes only and are not used for regulatory reporting purposes.</p> 

						<p>Buy market orders with a weighted average <a href="javascript:popLargerWin('https://scs.fidelity.com/webxpress/help/topics/help_definition_e.shtml#executionprice')">execution price</a> below the National Best Offer (NBO) are considered price improved. Price improvement for buy market orders is calculated by subtracting the weighted average execution price from the NBO, then multiplying by the number of executed shares to arrive at the net price improvement for the order. Price improvement on buy limit orders is calculated as the lesser of the NBO minus the execution price and the limit price minus the execution price. Sell market orders with a weighted average execution price above the National Best Bid (NBB) are considered price improved. Price improvement for sell market orders is calculated by subtracting the NBB from the weighted average execution price, then multiplying by the number of executed shares to arrive at the net price improvement for the order. Price improvement on sell limit orders is calculated as the lesser of the execution price minus the NBB and the execution price minus the limit price.</p> 
						
						<p>Prior to December 7, 2015, price improvement for limit orders (buy and sell) was calculated using the methodology for price improvement on market orders described above.</p>

				<div class="legal-footer--item-content-detail" id="legal-footer--price-improvement" style="display: none;">
				
						<p>Price improvement details provided for domestic stock and single leg option orders entered during market hours after the primary opening, provided there is a National Best Bid and Offer (NBBO) at the time the order is placed. Price improvement details are provided for informational purposes only and are not used for regulatory reporting purposes.</p> 

						<p>Buy market orders with a weighted average <a href="javascript:popLargerWin('https://scs.fidelity.com/webxpress/help/topics/help_definition_e.shtml#executionprice')">execution price</a> below the National Best Offer (NBO) are considered price improved. Price improvement for buy market orders is calculated by subtracting the weighted average execution price from the NBO, then multiplying by the number of executed shares to arrive at the net price improvement for the order. Price improvement on buy limit orders is calculated as the lesser of the NBO minus the execution price and the limit price minus the execution price. Sell market orders with a weighted average execution price above the National Best Bid (NBB) are considered price improved. Price improvement for sell market orders is calculated by subtracting the NBB from the weighted average execution price, then multiplying by the number of executed shares to arrive at the net price improvement for the order. Price improvement on sell limit orders is calculated as the lesser of the execution price minus the NBB and the execution price minus the limit price. </p> 
						
						<p>Prior to December 7, 2015, price improvement for limit orders (buy and sell) was calculated using the methodology for price improvement on market orders described above.</p>
						
						<p>Some orders may not receive any price improvement. Fast market conditions and large order sizes relative to the bid or ask size may result in shares executing at or outside the NBBO. To learn more about our commitment to execution quality, click <a href="javascript:popLargerWin('https://www.fidelity.com/trading/execution-quality/overview')">here.</a></p>
						
						<p>Total Price Improvement reflects the sum of net price improvements on eligible orders executed within the stated timeframe. Orders with a weighted average execution price above the ask (for buys) or below the bid (for sells) are not factored into the Total Price Improvement figures. See <a href="javascript:popLargerWin('https://www.fidelity.com/trading/faqs-placing-orders')">Trading FAQs <img src="https://www.fid-inv.com/webcontent/ap110184-client-portfolio/73.1/images/dev/popup_blue.gif" style="vertical-align: top;" class="account-selector-close-control--icon" alt="Open Trading FAQ" width="12" height="12" /></a> for more information.</p>
						 
				</div>			
				
			<!-- End of Price Improvement Phase 4 -->	
			<!-- Start of todays markets disclosure -->  
                 <div class="legal-footer--item-content-detail" id="legal-footer--todays-markets" style="display: none;">
                                 <p>Today's Markets provides access to quotes, delayed by 10 minutes, for select front-month futures contracts. The front-month contract will automatically roll to the next contract month upon expiration, when it has an open interest more than twice the current month, or its trading volume is larger.</p>
                 </div>
			<!-- End of todays markets disclosure  --> 
			
			<!-- Start of Retirement RPM disclosure -->  
                 <div class="legal-footer--item-content-detail" id="legal-footer--rpm" style="display: none;">
                                 <p><b>IMPORTANT: The projections or other information generated by the Planning & Guidance Center's Retirement Analysis regarding the likelihood of various investment outcomes are hypothetical in nature, do not reflect actual investment results, and are not guarantees of future results. Your results may vary with each use and over time.</b></p>
                 				 <p>Retirement Analysis, including the Retirement Preparedness Measure (RPM), is based on information you provided and certain assumptions, including market performance assumptions based on hypothetical scenarios using historical index data. Numerous factors make the calculations uncertain, such as the use of assumptions about historical returns and inflation, as well as the data you have provided. Fund fees and other expenses will generally reduce your actual investment returns and are generally not reflected in the hypothetical projections.</p>
                 </div>
			<!-- End of Retirement RPM disclosure disclosure  -->

				<p>The information contained in the CSV version of your tax forms is general in nature, and is provided for informational purposes only. The information reported may not reflect all adjustments necessary for tax reporting purposes, and may not be appropriate for use in preparing a tax return. You should use the official tax forms that Fidelity sends by mail for purposes of tax return preparation. Fidelity and National Financial Services (NFS) specifically disclaim any liability arising out of a customer's use of, or any tax position taken in reliance upon, such information.</p>
				<p>Unless otherwise specified, NFS determines cost basis at the time of sale based on the average cost method for open-end mutual funds and based on the first-in, first-out (FIFO) method for all other securities.</p>
				<p>A covered tax lot indicates that Fidelity will include cost basis and holding period information on the annual 1099-B for the year the tax lot is closed. Consult your tax advisor for further information.</p>
			</div>
			<!-- Statements End -->
